OL,3,CHow broke is your council?
OL,5,FAs young Lei'maie-Zhyon Richards takes
OL,6,Fto the stage to show the musical
OL,7,Fskills developed at a Handsworth youth
OL,8,Fproject, her mother says: "Kids as
OL,9,Fyoung as 15 are being killed over
OL,10,Fsenseless stuff ` when they could be
OL,11,Fin a community centre."
OL,13,FOn another, bigger stage across
OL,14,FBirmingham, Joe Lycett has a warning
OL,15,Ffor us all: "Dimming the lights is
OL,16,Ffunny, bins are funny. But I don't
OL,17,Fwant to be writing jokes about my city
OL,18,Fthat I love falling apart. I fear it's
OL,19,Fcoming to many more councils around
OL,20,Fthe country."
